\f0\fs24 \cf0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1 Today is the anniversary of the birth of 
\f2\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Werner Karl Heisenberg
\f1\b0  (1901-1976), 
\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56809 \u55356 \u56810 
\f1  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germans"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 German}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theoretical_physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 theoretical physicist}} and one of the key pioneers of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 quantum mechanics}}. He published his work in 1925 in a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%9Cber_quantentheoretische_Umdeutung_kinematischer_und_mechanischer_Beziehungen"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 breakthrough paper}}. In the subsequent series of papers with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Born"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Max Born}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pascual_Jordan"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Pascual Jordan}}, during the same year, this {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 matrix formulation}} of quantum mechanics was substantially elaborated. \
He is known for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uncertainty_principle"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Heisenberg uncertainty principle}}, which he published in 1927. Heisenberg was awarded the 1932 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Nobel Prize in Physics}} "for the creation of quantum mechanics".\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 He also made important contributions to the theories of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_dynamics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 hydrodynamics}} of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turbulent_flow"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 turbulent flows}}, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_nucleus"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 atomic nucleus}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ferromagnetism"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 ferromagnetism}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosmic_rays"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cosmic rays}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subatomic_particles"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 subatomic particles}}, and he was instrumental in planning the first West German {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_reactor"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 nuclear reactor}} at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karlsruhe"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Karlsruhe}}, together with a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_reactor"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 research reactor}} in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munich"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Munich}}, in 1957. He was a principal scientist in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_nuclear_weapons_program"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 German nuclear weapons program}} during {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 World War II}}. He travelled to occupied Copenhagen where he met and discussed the German project with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niels_Bohr"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 Niels Bohr}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 \

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f1 \'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della nascita di uno dei padri della meccanica quantistica, 
\f2\b Werner Karl Heisenberg
\f1\b0  (1901-1976), fisico 
\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56809 \u55356 \u56810 
\f1 tedesco\cb1  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premio_Nobel_per_la_fisica"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 premio Nobel per la fisica}}\cb3  nel 1932. \'c8 famoso per aver introdotto il celebre {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principio_di_indeterminazione_di_Heisenberg"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 principio di indeterminazione}}\cf4  (1927) e per aver sviluppato la formulazione matriciale della meccanica quantistica, rivelatasi essere equivalente a quella sviluppata indipendentemente da Erwin Schr\'f6dinger\cf2 . \
Nel 1925, infatti, un giovanissimo Heisenberg pubblica un articolo rivoluzionario che verr\'e0 poi sviluppato in una serie di articoli con Jordan e Max Born dando vita alla formulazione matriciale della meccanica quantistica. \
Fu il leader del piano nazista per la corsa all\'92atomica durante la seconda guerra mondiale. Rimane famosissimo il suo incontro con Niels Bohr a Copenhagen mentre la Danimarca era occupata dai nazisti. Heisenberg invit\'f2 l\'92amico Bohr a unirsi al programma scientifico nazista ma Bohr, non condividendo gli ideali nazional-socialisti, si rifiut\'f2. \
\
